Political leaders in the Ilorin East Local Government Area of Kwara State have called on the state governor, Abdulrahman Abdulrazak, to pay more attention to the rural areas in order to ensure even development of the state. The leaders, including chieftains of the ruling All Progressive Congress, led by Alhaji Musa Maiyaki (the Magajin Maiyaki of Ilorin), made the appeal in Ilorin, the state capital, at a stakeholders’ forum, which was also attended by traditional rulers in the area. A statement on Tuesday said the spokesman for the leaders at the forum, Alhaji A. S. Mahmud, noted that the rural segment of the local government needed urgent attention of the government. “Mahmud also said the leaders expressed their appreciation to the Abdulrazak administration for the infrastructural projects and development strides in education and health sectors in the council. “Many traditional leaders of the local government under the headship of the Balogun Gambari of Ilorin were present,’’ the statement said. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 